headline: DoorDash, Lyft, Upstart: Three Earnings In Focus
summary: Morning Brief hosts Seana Smith and Brad Smith outline the stock reactions following these companies' latest earnings results: Lyft (LYFT) stock falls further after its outlook disappointed Wall Street investors. DoorDash (DASH) shares move higher into positive territory on its fourth quarter earnings beat and strong guidance. Lastly, Upstart Holdings (UPST) soars by over 30% higher on Wednesday following the company's strong fourth quarter performance and guidance figures. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.
